            "body": "@clason For now, I found a way to reproduce a second error message  `'[LSP] No client with id 1'`. And also a new one `[LSP] Client with id 1 not attached to buffer 2`.\r\n\r\nWay to repro is hacky, I tried to simulate kinda project switching without actual plugins to do so.\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nsudo pacman -S rust-analyzer lua-language-server neovim\r\ncd /tmp/ && git clone https://github.com/coffebar/neovim-test.git \r\ncd neovim-test\r\nnvim -u ./init.lua\r\n```\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/3100053/71ab80c1-753a-4b9a-9cbf-b1392e4cb743)\r\n\r\nThe main code in the init.lua\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal i = 1000\r\nwhile i < 2500 do\r\n  vim.defer_fn(function()\r\n    vim.api.nvim_command(\"edit src/main.rs | cd .. | edit lua.lua | %bd | cd neovim-test\")\r\n  end, i)\r\n  vim.defer_fn(function()\r\n    vim.api.nvim_command(\"edit lua.lua | LspStop rust_analyzer\")\r\n  end, i + 100)\r\n  i = i + 500\r\nend\r\n\r\nvim.defer_fn(function()\r\n  vim.api.nvim_command(\"cd src | edit main.rs\")\r\nend, 3000)\r\n\r\nvim.defer_fn(function()\r\n  vim.api.nvim_command(\"cd .. | %bd | edit lua.lua\")\r\nend, 3091)\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaybe the way to reproduce is longer than it should be, actually, I saw this message every time when just opened neovim, but it will be a much more complicated config.",
